# Utility Function Naming Conventions

## Verification
Run `pnpm run cursor:verify` (includes utility naming check). Fix any reported files.

## Convention
- **Utility files under `app/.../utils` must use camelCase** (e.g. `handleNumericInput.ts`).
- File name should match the exported function name (except extension).
- PascalCase is reserved for React components.
- **Compound names** use the segment before the first dot as the primary name (e.g. `handleSubmit.util.ts` → `handleSubmit`).

## What `utility-naming.ts` skips (not function-style utilities)
- Test and spec files (`*.test.*`, `*.spec.*`), type modules (`*.type.ts`, `*.types.*`), constants (`*.constant(s).*`), `*.guardz.ts`, `*.dto.ts`, `*.enum.ts`
- Paths under `**/enums/**`, `**/form/validations/**`, `**/typeguards/**`

